    <note>Yue(1) Huangmu [2114] Shi's [4141] second son. Shi's grandson and Huangmu's son, Xuguo [4140], is said to have moved to Henan, but Shi probably made the move since by the time Yin(2) Zhu writes the funerary inscription for Xuguo's wife, the family is considered to be a great lineage (dazu) of Henan. Xuguo's son, Zi [11948], is still listed as a Fuzhou, Yihuang jinshi even though his brother, Yong [11949], a jinshi, is not listed and Zi's father Xuguo is clearly a Luoyang resident. Huangmu's niece was Chen(1) Jiansu's [7102] wife, who is also a Henan, Luoyang resident. Jiangxi TZ, 21.8b; XCB, 61.12b, 84.8a, 87.8b; Guangxi TZ, 16.7a; SS, 306.20a-20b; DDSL, 115.3b Yin Zhu, WJ, 15.6b. CBD, 5, 3829-30.</note>
